The article discusses a recent court decision in Texas that threatens women's rights to make decisions about their healthcare and access medication prescribed by their doctors. The decision undermines the FDA's ability to approve safe and effective medications based on science, not politics. This decision not only affects abortion rights but also the rights of all Americans to access FDA-approved medication. The article highlights the contrast between this decision and a different conclusion reached by a court in Washington state. The author emphasizes the importance of protecting reproductive freedom and the ability of individuals to make healthcare decisions with their doctors without political interference.